column2: One of the product doors is open.
1. Make sure that the door is completely closed. 2. If the error persists, replace the engine controller.
An internal communication error has occurred.
1. Verify that the connectors on the engine controller are seated firmly. 2. Replace the engine controller.
Engine error. Press OK to continue.
If the error persists, replace the engine controller.
Paper has jammed in the indicated location. Clear the jam, and then if the error persists, try the following solutions.
1. Verify the pickup roller and separation roller are working correctly and not damaged. If necessary, replace the rollers. 2. Verify that connector J116 on the engine controller is firmly seated.
The product does not detect paper in the tray.
1. Verify that paper is correctly loaded in the tray. 2. Verify that all engine controller connectors are firmly seated.
The product cannot process the page.
1. Perform an NVRAM initialization. 2. Update the firmware. 3. Replace the formatter PCA.

The product experienced an internal error.
1. Turn off the power by using the power switch, wait at least 30 seconds, and then turn on the power and wait for the product to initialize. 2. If the error persists, replace the formatter.
The fuser has experienced a problem.
1. Verify that connectors J104 and J110 on the engine controller are seated firmly. 2. Replace the fuser. 3. Replace the fuser power supply.

ITB or main motor rotation error (59.A0)
Image drum motor startup error - black
Image drum motor startup error - yellow
Image drum motor rotation error - black
Image drum motor rotation error - yellow
The product has experienced an internal firmware error.

1. Turn off the power by using the power switch, wait at least 30 seconds, and then turn on the power and wait for the product to initialize. 2. If a surge protector is being used, remove it. Plug the product directly into the wall socket. Use the power switch to turn the product on. 3. Replace the formatter.
